description: The Biden administration may release intelligence that  reveals that China is considering giving Russia weapons for the war in Ukraine.

title: Mystery over colourful by-the-wind-sailor washed up on Eagles Nest Beach in Victoria
description: A beachgoer took a picture of the unusual disc-shaped marine animal at Eagles Nest Beach on the Victorian south coast, asking people what it was.

title: Mick Lynch admits RMT ballot on pay deal which could have ended strikes was 'flawed', sources claim
description: Senior sources said Mr Lynch admitted in a meeting with industry leaders and the rail minister that his members did not have enough time to understand the complex offer.

title: Lidia Thorpe blows up at ABC host Patricia Karvelas for calling Linda Burnie a legend
description: In an awkward fiery interview on Radio National on Thursday morning, Indigenous senator Lidia Thorpe fired back at Patricia Karvelas: 'I don't hear you calling me a legend.'

title: Nathan Chasing Horse, 'Dances With Wolves' star, indicted on sexual assault charges involving teens
description: A Las Vegas grand jury has indicted 'Dances With Wolves' actor Nathan Chasing Horse on 19 charges of sexual assault, mostly involving victims under 16.

title: Furious Today Show blow-up as Jim Chalmers backs AWAY from radical superannuation shake-up
description: Dr Chalmers on Wednesday afternoon hosed down suggestions the Federal government will increase the tax rate on extra contributions to superannuation.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Is asylum plan really taking back control?
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: More than 150,000 people are being fed, housed and clothed at huge expense to the taxpayer while their claims are processed.

title: Sunnyvale tops the list of 10 happiest cities in America - 62% of residents earn $100,000
description: In fact, California was home to six of the top 10 cities on the list, which combines 13 different metrics across three categories: personal finance, well-being and quality of life.

title: Immutable crypto gaming start-up laying off 11 per cent of its staff
description: Crypto gaming start-up Immutable X, which raised $280million of venture capital resulting in it being valued at $3.5billion last March, has quietly moved to lay off 11 per cent of their employees.

title: New Video shows the terrifying moment alligator lunges at woman
description: Gloria Serge, 85, was walking her dog by the lake in the Spanish Lakes Fairways community in Fort Pierce, Florida on Monday when an alligator attacked her, dragging her into the water.

title: Meet the new generation of gold-diggers who manipulate dating app algorithms to bag a rich man
description: Amy Green, 27, just wants to find her ideal: a man who has his own place, is in a secure career - and, preferably, lives in Kensington. She and her friends change their Tinder geolocations.

title: Dozens of criminals walk free after escaping being fitted with electronic tags due to IT error
description: A controversial computer system in the courts, called Common Platform, failed to send out more than 3,000 messages to criminal justice agencies.

title: Why today is effectively the first day of the year women 'stop working for free'
description: Women effectively work for free for two months a year, with today marking the point when they finally no longer effectively work for free, because they are paid so much less than men, according to a report.

title: Keir Starmer announces five 'national missions'... but sidesteps small boat Channel crossings
description: Kier Starmer will set out five 'national missions' at a keynote speech in Manchester today in a push to cement the party's 28-point poll lead.
